**‚ì¶hat happens?**
> * Each week a new topic (like this one) is posted in the #contests category. > * If you want your track considered for track of the week, just post a link to your track below, before the due date listed at the bottom of this topic. > * The winner will be announced here at the end of the week.
**‚ì°ules:**
> 1. Track must be made by the submitter, using Auxy. > 2. There are no set themes. Any genre. Any tempo. Any automations. > 3. Tracks must be 60-seconds or longer. > 4. Tracks submitted must premiere the week of the TotW posted. > 5. One entry per person, per week. > 6. No collabs or remixes. > 7. You can edit your post during the week if you make updates to your submission. > 8. External samples can be used for individual instruments or vocals only > ie: not sections of sampled music or drum loops. > 9. Project files won‚Äôt be considered - **judges reserve the right to see project files if the legitimacy of the track is in question!** > 10. Late entries won‚Äôt be considered. Enter in the next week instead. > 11. Please also create a thread for your track under #tracks, like usual, if you wish.
**‚ìôudging:** One winner is chosen each week, or possibly a draw. Judging will be totally subjective. Please don‚Äôt ask why your track didn‚Äôt win. The judges alternate between: -
* cursed * blakkaz * AzureOnyx * MrSerpent * Mr_Mooo * zhandermusic * Peregrihn * Dadmother * HexxOfficial * Goxenar
Judge this week is: @Mr_Mooo
**‚ìürize**
* Winner gets a special :cd: icon next to their forum name. * Winner‚Äôs name is also listed in a [winner‚Äôs thread](https://disco.auxy.co/t/auxy-forum-track-of-the-week-winners/15961).
**PLEASE NOTE: If you change your title in profile settings from ‚Äúblank‚Äù to Regular, or vice versa, YOU WILL LOSE ALL CDS AND UNICORNS!**

item.dc:creator: ThoughtfulNoise
item.description:
Yeah, sorry, didn‚Äôt mean to put it to you like it was your problem to solve.

Wondering if it might be time for a period of ‚Äòno mod‚Äô, to let it become whatever it becomes, even if that means letting it die, and let Auxy deal with it. After all, it‚Äôs a free community attached to their commercial business. The Auxy team are the ones with all the incentives - brand, salaries, etc‚Ä¶

‚Ä¶or maybe just have a mod or two who are keen but who ,will need to demonstrate their reliability while ‚Äòon the job‚Äô.

Either way, it‚Äôs not something your conscientiousness should compel you to worry about or figure out.

Those who have freely given their time and effort as mods here have gone above and beyond. Maybe it‚Äôs time for the salaried ones to step up.

item.title: Auxy Forum - Track of the Week #49 [10/12 - 10/19] (Winner Announced)
item.dc:creator: iammane
item.description:
ThoughtfulNoise:

Surely there‚Äôs someone else (as well as, rather than instead of) who can be trusted and is willing to carry some of the weight?

I‚Äôll be super transparent here - the folks I would have said were a good fit have all moved on.

Lenberg is (seemingly) not super crazy about having a ton of people with administrative capabilities (ie, in order to change titles to give out unicorns and discs and stuff, you can‚Äôt just be a leader - you have to be added to a specific permission/role group). Otherwise other folks can be promoted to leader and the discourse platform will allow thread closing/merging etc, but no one would be able to really drive a contest or etc in any meaningful way.

I approached Dadmo about it and I think real life just kicked into gear - it‚Äôs what happens. I know my time ebbs and flows, lately it‚Äôs been a struggle with work projects really starting to take off. I think he sincerely has the best intentions for this place, but yeah - life gonna do what life gonna do.

Truthfully, I don‚Äôt know anymore who else would be a good fit.

I hear ya on discord servers. Myself I‚Äôm in only two cause I just can‚Äôt keep up, and I can‚Äôt be bothered. I think the chaps over there are doing a good job though, the feedback for feedback channel works pretty well, and the weekly feedback streams are very popular. But‚Ä¶ I totally understand your sentiment lol‚Ä¶

Read full topic

item.dc:creator: ThoughtfulNoise
item.description:
Bit confused why dadmom put their hand up for mod duties if time was v limited. Surely there‚Äôs someone else (as well as, rather than instead of) who can be trusted and is willing to carry some of the weight?

 
Re: Discord servers

Tbh, maybe my age, but I find Discord servers a bit too all over the joint, and imo, they lend themselves much more to soundbites, rather than something longer and more considered.

I struggle to get a sense that it‚Äôs an experience where meaningful feedback can be shared, and where meaningful growth can be fostered.

Not a boomer, but I certainly feel like one when I walk through those doors.

Still, maybe one more try‚Ä¶

item.dc:creator: iammane
item.description:
I‚Äôm trying to distance myself from (responsibility around) here, and I know Dadmo is incredibly, incredibly busy with work and life in general, so track of the week may become track of the week it‚Äôs posted, if you‚Äôre picking up what I‚Äôm putting down.

It‚Äôs no secret things have slowed down around here quite a bit, for various reasons. I would point anyone looking for more interaction toward the Auxy Collective discord server. There‚Äôs weekly feedback streams, an award ceremony called the ACCAs where submitted tracks are voted on, etc. It‚Äôs also not Auxy exclusive, which is neat. There‚Äôs a lot of familiar faces over there, a lot of folks you don‚Äôt see around here anymore.
